comments.body:
Yeah, sounds like we should provide some warnings. For each of the following cases, can you clarify what you mean by "some listener ports"? Which ones?

 for some listener ports, the security group(s) do not authorize the ports (probably red flag)
 for some listener ports, the security groups(s) authorize them, but CIDR is not for public (yellow flag?)
 the security group(s) have the ports open that is not one of the listener ports (yellow flag? because the group might be used for other applications too).

[~kgill], this bug is starting to turn into too much work for 4.3.1. I'll open a companion bug for 4.4 (opened GUI-2747 and linked to this ticket) for the security group warning stuff, but this bug should just define the ports and take the user to the security groups page. 

We should be sure the warning only displays for VPC ELBs, and that this displays AFTER the call to create the ELB is made. Remove the checkbox and change the submit button text to "Take Me to My Security Groups". Close button should take the user to ELB details for the new ELB.
